        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 8:45PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 844 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles south of Turner, or 32 miles northwest of Malta, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of eastern Blaine
County.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
